RwandAir is celebrating four years of flying into Abuja from Kigali, capital of Rwanda. The inaugural flight on one of the carrier’s Boeing 737-800s, took place on April 27, 2018. According to Nigeria’s Country Manager of the airline, Muhamud Wayiga, in the four years of operating, RwandAir has flown more than 47,000 customers to and from Abuja. He said: “Nigeria is a hugely important market for RwandAir so we are very happy to be celebrating four highly successful years of flying to Abuja, the country’s second city. “Our flights have kept pace with customer demand, continue to offer fantastic connectivity to destinations across Africa and has strengthened business opportunities between Rwandans and Nigerians who have greatly benefited from the visa-free policy. “We thank all of our customers for choosing to fly with us on the route and are pleased to continue connecting these two great cities.” RwandAir currently serves 28 destinations across East, Central, West and Southern Africa, the Middle East, Europe and Asia.